# 📊 Business Impact Analysis (BIA)

## 🔹 Process Details
| Field | Description |
|------|-------------|
| Process Name | Name of the business/service process |
| Business Unit | Department owning the process |
| Process Owner | Responsible leader/contact |
| Criticality Level | High / Medium / Low |

---

## 🔹 Impact Assessment
| Field | Description |
|------|-------------|
| Financial Impact | Revenue loss, penalties, cost impact |
| Operational Impact | Service disruption, backlog, productivity loss |
| Customer Impact | SLA breach, customer dissatisfaction |
| Regulatory Impact | Compliance/legal risks |

---

## 🔹 Recovery Objectives
| Field | Description |
|------|-------------|
| RTO (Recovery Time Objective) | Max acceptable downtime |
| RPO (Recovery Point Objective) | Max acceptable data loss |
| MTD (Maximum Tolerable Downtime) | Absolute limit before severe damage |

---

## 🔹 Dependencies
| Type | Details |
|------|--------|
| Applications | Systems/tools required |
| Infrastructure | Servers, network, cloud |
| People | Key roles/teams required |
| Vendors | External dependencies |

---

## 🔹 Risk Assessment
| Field | Description |
|------|-------------|
| Risk Scenario | Example: Data center outage |
| Likelihood | High / Medium / Low |
| Impact Severity | High / Medium / Low |
| Risk Rating | Combined score |

---

## 🔹 Recovery Strategy
| Field | Description |
|------|-------------|
| Recovery Approach | Manual workaround / Failover / Backup system |
| Alternate Site | DR site / Remote operations |
| Recovery Steps | High-level recovery actions |

---

## 🔹 Communication Plan
| Field | Description |
|------|-------------|
| Internal Stakeholders | Teams to notify |
| External Stakeholders | Customers/vendors |
| Communication Channel | Email / Bridge call / Dashboard |

---

## 🔹 Approval & Review
| Field | Description |
|------|-------------|
| Prepared By | Analyst name |
| Reviewed By | Leadership / Risk team |
| Last Updated | Date |
